    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures, labeled Figure 1 and Figure 2, each show a horizontal wire carrying current I to the right through the center of a circle with its plane oriented perpendicular to the wire. The circle in figure 1 has area A, and the circle in figure 2 has area 2 A.\" src=\"/images/c2c55f5882c7c5adb5a73cfdbd47ffe8.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> shows a wire with current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I\"><math alttext=\"I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>I</mi></math></span></span> to the right passing through the center of a circle having area <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>A</mi></math></span></span>. The plane of the circle is oriented perpendicular to the wire. The magnetic field at a location on the perimeter of the circle has magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>B</mi></math></span></span>. Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> shows the same wire passing through the center of a circle having area <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 A\"><math alttext=\"2 A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>A</mi></math></span></span>. Which of the following represents the magnetic field at a location on the perimeter of the circle in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> ?</p>\n",
